				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Of course it's not relevant for emulation, unless you are dealing with a ROM that should be mapper 206.<br /><br />My interest is purely in having unambiguous NES headers. Given that iNES and NES 2.0 do not explicitly denote mapper-controlled mirroring, what should the mirroring bit be for those games? I don't like &quot;Whatever, doesn't matter&quot;, because it means that the same game can have two different headers that are both correct.<br /><br />I can live with either &quot;Mapper-controlled mirroring means that Mirroring is not fixed to Vertical, so the bit must be zero&quot; or &quot;The mirroring bit should reflect the initial state of the mapper-controlled mirroring&quot;; just pick one and make it official.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

